---
name: coroutine-error
description: Coroutine — error propagation and nested coroutines
backends: [int, js, v2]
---

# Coroutine — error propagation

```scalascript
val co = coroutineCreate[Int, Unit, String] { () =>
  suspend(1)
  throw new RuntimeException("boom")
}
println(coroutineResume(co, ()))
val r = coroutineResume(co, ())
r match
  case Errored(_) => println("got-error")
  case _          => println("unexpected")
```

# Coroutine — nested (outer resumes inner)

```scalascript
val outer = coroutineCreate[Int, Unit, String] { () =>
  val inner = coroutineCreate[Int, Unit, String] { () =>
    suspend(99)
    "inner-done"
  }
  val step = coroutineResume(inner, ())
  step match
    case Yielded(v) =>
      suspend(v)
      ()
    case _ => ()
  "outer-done"
}
println(coroutineResume(outer, ()))
println(coroutineResume(outer, ()))
```
